<H2>Geometry Courses and Teaching Materials</H2>

<B>Computational geometry textbooks:</B>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.springer.de/catalog/html-files/deutsch/comp/354013722X.html">Algorithms in Combinatorial Geometry</A>, H. Edelsbrunner.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.springer.de/catalog/html-files/deutsch/comp/3540961313.html">Computational Geometry: An Introduction</A>, F. Preparata and M. Shamos.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.prenhall.com/~ray/013/336362/33636-2.html">Computational Geometry: An Introduction through Randomized Algorithms</A>, K. Mulmuley.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.prenhall.com/~ray/013/290841/29084-1.html">Computational Geometry and Computer Graphics in C++</A>, M. Laszlo.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cup.org/Titles/44/0521440343.html">Computational Geometry in C</A>, J. O'Rourke [also see O'Rourke's
<A HREF="ftp://grendel.csc.smith.edu/pub/compgeom/">online errata and
source code</A>].
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cup.org/Titles/47/0521470250.html">Davenport-Schinzel Sequences and their Geometric Applications</A>, M. Sharir and P. Agarwal.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.prenhall.com/~ray/013/652016/65201-6.html">Parallel Computational Geometry</A>, S. Akl.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Computational geometry courses:</B>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cs.brown.edu/courses/cs252/">Brown U., CS 252, computational geometry</A>.
